OL,3,CFarmer with giant hernia going private
OL,4,Cafter five year wait for NHS operation
OL,6,FSpeaking at an event in London on
OL,7,FThursday, the prime minister said:
OL,8,F"The NHS is at a fork in the road, and
OL,9,Fwe have a choice about how it should
OL,10,Fmeet these rising demands.
OL,12,F"Raise taxes on working people to meet
OL,13,Fthe ever-higher costs of an ageing
OL,14,Fpopulation - or reform to secure its
OL,15,Ffuture.
OL,17,F"We know working people can't afford
OL,18,Fto pay more, so it's reform or die."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
